headline: Microchip Stock Doubled In The Last 2 Months. Can It Keep On Flying?
summary: Shares of memory-chip maker Microchip Technology fell early this year in sync with the rest of the market.  Its strength earned Microchip stock a Relative Strength Rating upgrade from 69 to 80 Monday, crossing above a key benchmark.  Despite its extraordinary performance in the last two months, Microchip stock has a long growth runway ahead.
